abstract: The majority leader — who has proved adept at the hand-to-hand procedural combat of the Senate, frustrating Democrats at every turn — had been preparing for a trial for nearly a year.
snippet: The majority leader — who has proved adept at the hand-to-hand procedural combat of the Senate, frustrating Democrats at every turn — had been preparing for a trial for nearly a year.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — On a Tuesday afternoon a week into President Trump’s impeachment trial, Senator Mitch McConnell could see his carefully laid plan to deliver a swift acquittal veering off the rails.

abstract: A day after his acquittal, the president took a victory lap, and vented, in a wild White House speech.
snippet: A day after his acquittal, the president took a victory lap, and vented, in a wild White House speech.
lead_paragraph: “I’m really not a bad person,” Mr. Trump said about an hour into his speech this afternoon, his eyes searching the crowd for a response.

abstract: Michael Bloomberg has sworn off taking money from other people for his presidential campaign. But in private, he is courting rich Democrats, potentially posing a challenge for his moderate rivals.
snippet: Michael Bloomberg has sworn off taking money from other people for his presidential campaign. But in private, he is courting rich Democrats, potentially posing a challenge for his moderate rivals.
lead_paragraph: MANCHESTER, N.H. — In the middle of January, most Democratic presidential candidates were scrambling to raise money to keep their campaigns afloat. But at an airy gallery in downtown San Francisco, Michael R. Bloomberg gathered a group of several dozen local political donors to make a different kind of appeal.

abstract: The Treasury Department complied with a request from Senate Republicans for documents related to Hunter Biden’s ties to a Ukrainian energy company, according to a Senate Democrat.
snippet: The Treasury Department complied with a request from Senate Republicans for documents related to Hunter Biden’s ties to a Ukrainian energy company, according to a Senate Democrat.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — In the wake of the Senate acquitting President Trump in an impeachment trial over his efforts to pressure Ukraine to investigate his political rivals including former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr., Republican senators are pressing ahead with their probes into the finances of Mr. Biden’s son, Hunter Biden.

abstract: As President Trump renewed his attacks on Speaker Nancy Pelosi and Democrats, his press secretary threatened payback against them.
snippet: As President Trump renewed his attacks on Speaker Nancy Pelosi and Democrats, his press secretary threatened payback against them.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump and his Republican allies focused on exacting payback against his political opponents on Thursday after his acquittal in his Senate impeachment trial, signaling that the conflict that has consumed Washington for months may only escalate rather than recede.
